<p> Since the start of the war, <span style="color:#e71e25">Russia</span> has lost over 9,000 items of military equipment such as tanks, artillery and aircraft, according to open-source defence site Oryx. <br><br> <span style="color:#2880c2">Ukraineâ€™s</span> losses amount to just under 3,000. <a href="#story/1831546/slide-1"></a></p>

 

<p> <span style="color:#2880c2">Ukraine</span> losses include 155 self-propelled artillery and 99 towed artillery systems. These include 43 Soviet era self-propelled 122mm 2S1 Gvozdikas and 39 American towed 155mm M777A2 howitzers. <a href="#story/1831546/slide-2"></a></p>

 

<p> <span style="color:#e71e25">Russia</span> has lost three times more self-propelled artillery systems than <span style="color:#2880c2">Ukraine</span> and nearly two times more towed artillery systems. <a href="#story/1831546/slide-3"></a></p>

 

<p> Since the beginning of the invasion, <span style="color:#e71e25">Russia</span> has been losing around five tanks per day. So far, they have lost almost four times as many tanks as <span style="color:#2880c2">Ukraine</span>.    <a href="#story/1831546/slide-4"></a></p>

 

